About
Since opening its doors in 2003, Base Elements has functioned as a multi-faceted gallery- acting as both a workshop and studio- where space and forum collide.There is no doubt that Barcelona is one of the world’s hubs for Graffiti and Street Art. The walls and buildings of the city have become a canvas for both unknown taggers and globally known urban artists. With the concept of providing a literal and figurative canvas for such independent artists, Robert Burt (California native) and his wife Monica Riu (Barcelona Native) founded Base Elements Urban Art Gallery in 2003 with hopes of creating a space where such street artists could not only showcase their talents, but also be embraced as true artists.

The area

Address
Neighborhood: Barrio Gòtico (Barri Gòtic)
With its iconic, old-Europe streets and alleys, this picturesque neighborhood is the very heart of Barcelona. It blends historic artifacts from its days under Roman dominion up through the Spanish Civil War with a vibrant modern-day culture of artisan shops and authentic culinary experiences. Avid explorers will be thrilled to discover quaint terraces and plazas brought to life by the many small bars and local musicians lasting late into the night. Fashionistas will be drawn to Portal de L’Angel, which is lined with well-known brand names and smaller boutique stands.

Highly recommended urban contemporary art gallery at Barcelona
Aug 2024 • Friends
In the tangled web that connects urban artists with public and private institutions and the general public, urban art is the thread that balances on the fine line of a tightrope. If in the public space your presence is ephemeral, in the private sphere it is the gallery that mediates and helps you cross the bridge that will take you to the artist so that his work (contemporary and boldly urban) becomes part of your intimacy. Just walk past it, without even having entered yet, and you will be struck by the contrasting dichotomy between timeless urban art inserted in a place built over a hundred years ago, which represents an authentic public heritage of the history of this city. And this is just one of the addresses of this gallery (Carrer del Avinnyo, 31) that has a double life (the other address is Carrer del Palau, 4, two blocks apart). The gallery at the last mentioned address also has surprises. At any moment, you may find one of the artists represented creating with the doors open and you may have the incredible opportunity to witness one of these unique moments and, as a bonus, meet one of these radiant human beings in action. The person responsible for the chemical reaction that makes this creative mix possible is the owner, founder and agent, Robert Burt. It is impossible to leave this experience, however it presents itself to you, without the relevant impact that will mark your contemporary criteria. I recommend it as a resident of the city, a neighbor of the gallery and an integrated participant in the latent life of this Barcelona that welcomes me every day.
Written August 11, 2024

Fabulous insight into Street art into the gallery
May 2023 • Couples
I don’t know much about street art, but
Having been introduced to it yesterday (on an also excellent Sandeman tour featuring Andy Pitt) and visited one of the two close by Base Elements Street art galleries, we went back today and saw the other one. We met Roberto - the gallery owner who talked to us in depth about one of the artists featured in his gallery ‘El Pez’ and particularly his augmented reality pictures which are really interesting (pictures you can bring to further life using technology). el Pez was just one of many now famous street artists exhibiting in these galleries, and the quality of their craft just oozes from the canvases. Cannot recommend them enough, and if you are lucky enough to meet Roberto or one of his resident artists, you will have a rewarding and informative vist.

Art as it should be
Mar 2023
We bought our piso in Barcelona last April. We took our time and visisted multiple galleries for art to complete our decor. We were delighted to find Base Elements. The first piece we aquired was on display in their gallery. It was perfection. It was unique. It was stunning. After speaking with Robert, the gallery owner and curator, he provided us with the background of the work, the history of the artist, and his own thoughts of what we were seeking for our place. After buying this major piece for our home, we decided to add another work from Base Elements. This time though, we had a piece commisioned. From the outset, Robert listened to what we were attempting to achieve. Robert gave us his opinions and guided us in the process. He was in touch with the artist and was able to communicate what our needs were. We felt like Robert couldn't have been more attentive. He was invaluable in getting for us the piece we invisioned. The piece we commisioned is superb. I just can't imagine our piso without the art we acquired from Base Elemants. Stop by and let yourself be enveloped by what Base Elemants has to offer. I am sure we will have to add another selection soon.

Absolute Must in BCN
Oct 2021
My husband and I fell in love with street art in Barcelona - I mean, how can you not? It's so fun and colorful, and the city has so much talent! It's all captured and embodied in this amazing art gallery. Not only a showcase of local talent, but it's also a live exhibit with BCN's artists painting right there in the store! It's incredible. Not only that, but the owner was passionate and friendly. He took the time to introduce us to the artists (one of us who gave us an INCREDIBLE free sticker of this art - so cool!), showed us around the store and talked to us about the pieces and their creators, and even gave us this amazing piece of art from one of his artists who did a performance piece at burning man that my husband wants to frame now haha. This store is a must visit while in Barcelona, and in my opinion some of the best souvenirs your can bring back from your trip and appreciate over a lifetime.
